label: GE 28169 / Jasco 28168
info_overview:
Z-wave controlled AC outlet for standard incandescent lighting, CFL/LEDs, fans or small appliances.
Must not exceed 600 watts (Incandescent); 1800W (15A) Resistive or ½ HP Motor
info_inclusion: Put controller into inclusion mode, single press and release the manual/program button on the smart switch to include it in the network
info_exclusion: Put controller into exclusion mode, single press and release the manual/program button on the smart switch to exclude it from the network

options.label: LED Light on when Z-Wave turned OFF (Default)
LED Light on when Z-Wave turned On

associations.label: Single Press Button
associations.description: Sends message directly to configured node on single press of button.
associations.overview: This device will send a Basic Set Message directly to whatever Z-wave device you have mapped this setting to when you single press the on/off button. For example, if you map this setting to a wall switch and then single press the on/off button on this "Plug in Smart Switch," a corresponding on/off message will be sent directly to that wall switch, bypassing openHAB.

associations.label: Double Press button
associations.description: Sends message directly to configured node on double press of button.
associations.overview: This device will send a Basic Set Message directly to whatever Z-wave device you have mapped this setting to when you double press the on/off button. For example, if you map this setting to a wall switch and then double press the on/off button on this "Plug in Smart Switch," a corresponding on/off message will be sent directly to that wall switch, bypassing openHAB.
